      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by an independent analyst; checklist-based review documented.",
      "rationale": "Pre-simulation setup checklist (boundary conditions, mesh quality metrics, solver settings) reviewed and signed off by a second analyst independent of the primary modeller. Review report USE-REV-2024-03 archived in the project DMS."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by physics of the flow regime; sensitivity to model choice documented.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω selected based on documented performance for rotating machinery with adverse pressure gradients. Sensitivity study comparing SST k-ω, realizable k-ε, and RSM shows < 7% variation in RHI. SST k-ω consistently closest to PIV data. Selection rationale documented in MFR-2024-01."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity analysis on uncertain input parameters (fluid viscosity, rotational speed tolerance, geometric tolerances) with quantified impact on RHI.",
      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed on five key inputs: dynamic viscosity (±5%), rotational speed (±2%), inlet flow rate (±3%), impeller tip clearance (±0.05 mm), and hemolysis model coefficients (±10%). RHI sensitivity to hemolysis model coefficients is largest (±9.2%); all others < 5%. Uncertainty budget documented in UQ-RPT-2024-02."
    },
